<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[170,796,1914,2131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
This species was described and remains known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[231,291,1946,1971]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[303,463,1946,1971]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
). The original description provided only a drawing of a male, probably the 
<typeStatus box="[688,791,1978,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
. The female was never illustrated, and the only known specimen of this sex was destroyed during the fire in the MNRJ. Herein we illustrate both sexes of this species (including the male 
<typeStatus box="[363,467,2106,2131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
